WEBVTT

00:45.120 --> 00:47.031
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

01:01.240 --> 01:03.151
(GRASS RUSTLING)

01:05.200 --> 01:07.316
(PANTING)

01:10.960 --> 01:15.397
(CAITLIN GASPING)

01:25.920 --> 01:26.955
(SCREAMING)

01:30.760 --> 01:33.320
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

01:36.040 --> 01:37.838
MIDWIFEI It's a girl.

01:37.960 --> 01:39.394
(BABY CRYING)

01:46.280 --> 01:47.679
(CONTINUES CRYING)

01:51.240 --> 01:53.675
(CAITLIN GASPING)

01:54.680 --> 01:55.750
(SCREAMS)

01:55.840 --> 01:57.160
WALTER: Another one?

02:05.040 --> 02:06.519
(BABY CRYING)

02:12.000 --> 02:13.434
It's a boy.

02:14.400 --> 02:17.313
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

02:22.480 --> 02:26.360
CAITLINI Walter? (GASPING)

02:26.720 --> 02:29.678
(BABIES CRYING)

02:30.080 --> 02:32.674
(GROANING)

02:41.480 --> 02:44.233
(GASPING)

02:55.720 --> 02:58.872
They're bewitched.
Those children are marked.

02:59.040 --> 03:00.235
(DOOR OPENS)

03:01.240 --> 03:02.594
(DOOR CLOSES)

03:16.840 --> 03:20.117
(BABIES CRYING)

03:24.800 --> 03:27.792
(PANTING)

03:39.280 --> 03:42.750
(BELL TOLLING)

03:42.920 --> 03:45.594
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

03:50.840 --> 03:52.672
OSMUND: It's been
a hard night.

03:53.760 --> 03:55.114
The end is near.

04:04.440 --> 04:08.638
COUNCILOR MARRAKAR: We have waited too
long to choose King Gareth's successor.

04:08.720 --> 04:11.234
OSMUND: No one can convince the
King to stop searching for his son.

04:12.120 --> 04:14.555
And to give up hope that
Walter might be reconciled

04:14.640 --> 04:16.392
to take his place
as rightful heir.

04:16.680 --> 04:19.593
Walter is not coming back,
Brother Osmund.

04:19.680 --> 04:23.560
If His Majesty dies today,
the land has no crown,

04:23.800 --> 04:25.632
and no dragon to defend it.

04:26.520 --> 04:28.193
Unless, of course,
you have evidence

04:28.280 --> 04:29.873
to suggest
Drago might survive?

04:31.280 --> 04:32.600
I'm afraid not.

04:33.160 --> 04:34.833
The Queen passed
when her dragon died.

04:35.440 --> 04:38.512
A shared heart will
always mean shared pain.

04:40.400 --> 04:41.834
And a shared death.

04:42.880 --> 04:45.156
(KING GARETH
BREATHING RAGGEDLY)

04:50.320 --> 04:54.359
COUNCILOR MARRAKAR: Brother Osmund,
I can count on your support?

04:55.560 --> 04:59.679
Councilor, shouldn't Drago choose
a successor if the King cannot?

04:59.760 --> 05:02.036
Drago had his chance.

05:02.560 --> 05:05.120
We need a strong leader
on the throne,

05:05.240 --> 05:07.550
and I am the best candidate.

05:08.240 --> 05:09.355
DRAGO: Perhaps, you're right.

05:10.720 --> 05:12.552
Drago, lam honored
by your...

05:12.640 --> 05:14.756
DRAGO: I did have my chance.

05:16.480 --> 05:19.279
We shared many adventures.

05:19.360 --> 05:21.920
Built a castle into the sky.

05:22.000 --> 05:27.029
Lived by the Old Code and raised
a new generation of dragons.

05:28.240 --> 05:31.437
Truly, he was exceptional.

05:32.960 --> 05:34.758
(SIGHS)

05:43.200 --> 05:44.873
(WHISPERS)
Through this unction,

05:45.680 --> 05:48.911
may the Lord pardon thee for
whatever sins thou hast committed.

06:00.120 --> 06:02.191
Through this unction,

06:02.280 --> 06:05.636
may the Lord pardon thee for
whatever sins thou hast committed.

06:07.960 --> 06:12.477
May blessings be upon thee
both in the hereafter.

06:12.600 --> 06:14.557
DRAGO: Of the King,
it is certain.

06:14.640 --> 06:20.431
But in the matter of his son, I can't
help but think that I let him down.

06:20.520 --> 06:23.034
His Majesty never
spoke a word against you.

06:23.120 --> 06:27.671
Yet, I consider the rift in his
family my greatest failure.

06:27.760 --> 06:28.875
(SNIFFLES)

06:28.960 --> 06:31.713
When I die,
I will not be surprised

06:31.800 --> 06:34.553
if the great dragons
in the stars

06:34.640 --> 06:38.235
turn my spirit away
from a place among them.

06:38.640 --> 06:40.313
And what about the crown?

06:40.400 --> 06:42.676
Speak now,
before it is too late.

06:42.800 --> 06:44.154
(HEART BEATING)

06:44.240 --> 06:47.153
(KING GARETH GASPING WEAKLY)

06:47.600 --> 06:50.672
(HEART STOPS BEATING)
(MOANS)

06:51.040 --> 06:56.353
(DRAGO BREATHES DEEPLY)

07:07.200 --> 07:11.717
lam still bonded.

07:11.840 --> 07:14.480
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

07:21.200 --> 07:22.235
With whom?

07:22.840 --> 07:24.114
I can't tell.

07:24.200 --> 07:26.999
It's different
than before...

07:27.080 --> 07:28.309
Faint.

07:28.400 --> 07:32.439
Forgive me for leaving you, but
I must find out who it is.

07:32.520 --> 07:35.751
(WINGS FLAPPING LOUDLY)

07:40.560 --> 07:43.029
(MAN GRUNTING)

07:45.240 --> 07:46.389
Let's go for a walk.
(BONES CRACKING)

07:47.160 --> 07:48.958
(GROANING)

07:51.240 --> 07:52.275
(SPITS)

07:53.160 --> 07:54.230
Hmm.

07:55.040 --> 07:56.713
(GROANS)

07:57.360 --> 07:59.874
(WHISTLING)

08:00.040 --> 08:01.314
(GRUNTING)

08:01.400 --> 08:03.596
Peter, how's your sister?

08:05.080 --> 08:06.115
(BONES CRACKING)
(GROANS)

08:07.400 --> 08:09.471
(MEN GRUNTING)

08:18.840 --> 08:20.353
(SCREAMS)

08:21.840 --> 08:22.875
Come on.

08:23.440 --> 08:25.033
(CHOKING)

08:26.320 --> 08:27.390
Which way?

08:27.480 --> 08:28.515
Okay-

08:28.720 --> 08:30.631
(SCREAMS)

08:30.760 --> 08:32.114
(BELL TOLLS)

08:32.440 --> 08:33.999
(CHEERING)

08:38.240 --> 08:39.913
You're welcome.

08:40.039 --> 08:42.554
They always forget, you
need four to take me down.

08:45.840 --> 08:47.160
VILLAGER 1: Our hero!

08:48.120 --> 08:49.679
VILLAGER 2: Come here, boy,
have a look!

08:50.800 --> 08:52.393
BOY: My hero, Edric!

08:54.080 --> 08:55.514
VILLAGERI Sheriff!

08:55.600 --> 08:57.830
Blackmoor's barricaded
himself in the barn.

08:58.400 --> 08:59.435
ExceHenL

09:19.520 --> 09:20.555
Blackmoor!

09:21.280 --> 09:23.191
You are charged with
murder and banditry

09:23.280 --> 09:24.679
within the Shire
of Earl Robert Cole.

09:24.760 --> 09:26.671
I am, as you know,
his sheriff...

09:26.760 --> 09:29.229
(SCOFFS)
More like his arse-boy!

09:29.720 --> 09:30.869
(BLACKMOOR LAUGHS)

09:31.120 --> 09:32.474
Okay. What are you doing?

09:32.840 --> 09:34.638
I'm gonna burn him out.
Where's the fun in that?

09:36.840 --> 09:38.160
VILLAGERS: Get him, Edric!
Get him, Edric!

09:38.320 --> 09:39.913
(GRUNTS)

09:42.080 --> 09:44.549
(BLOWS LANDING)
EDRICI Wh00!

09:45.840 --> 09:47.990
(ALL CHEERING)

09:50.240 --> 09:52.151
Just doing my duty.
Here!

09:52.240 --> 09:54.151
Just doing my duty.
For you.

09:54.280 --> 09:56.271
Oh, really? No, I can't.
Thank you.

09:56.360 --> 09:57.509
You're too kind.
Thank you so much.

09:57.640 --> 09:58.675
You're too kind.

09:59.760 --> 10:01.831
EDRIC: I couldn't do it without you.
Couldn't do it.

10:01.960 --> 10:02.995
No way.

10:03.120 --> 10:04.349
No way, no how.

10:05.200 --> 10:06.190
My Lord.

10:07.200 --> 10:08.235
Ed ric.

10:08.360 --> 10:11.000
(CROVVD CCDNTINUES APPLAUDING) Thank you.
Couldn't do it without you.

10:13.600 --> 10:14.874
Well done, Edric.

10:15.440 --> 10:19.149
Profits will be up with that lot
finally dangling from a noose.

10:20.800 --> 10:21.835
EDRICI Oh.

10:22.040 --> 10:23.110
What's wrong, Edric?

10:23.200 --> 10:24.270
Excuse me.

10:25.800 --> 10:28.360
DRAGO: Feel like
you're being watched?

10:30.320 --> 10:33.199
It feels like I'm being judged.
Stay behind me, My Lord.

10:33.320 --> 10:35.550
Wait, I mean you no harm.

10:35.640 --> 10:37.313
Dragons do nothing but harm!

10:39.800 --> 10:40.835
(GRUNTS)

10:43.960 --> 10:46.793
<i>(ROARS)</i>

10:46.880 --> 10:47.870
(SCOFFS)

10:48.080 --> 10:49.070
(GROANS)

10:49.200 --> 10:50.235
EDRIC: Easy.

10:50.320 --> 10:52.231
Edric the Mighty, is it?

10:52.360 --> 10:55.876
I'll admit you've got
the strength of two men.

10:57.640 --> 10:58.914
It's three.

10:59.400 --> 11:00.549
(GRUNTS)

11:03.920 --> 11:06.309
And a flair for showing off.

11:06.400 --> 11:07.754
Stand and fight,

11:07.880 --> 11:11.157
so I can end whatever sorcery
you're using to see inside my soul.

11:11.240 --> 11:13.231
Maybe I'll just roast you!

11:13.360 --> 11:14.589
You see?

11:14.680 --> 11:17.433
A dragon's first impulse
is violence.

11:17.560 --> 11:20.757
Just as my father taught me, you were
born to kill, not to take care of us.

11:20.840 --> 11:22.592
Your father
is teaching you lies.

11:22.680 --> 11:23.875
And now you speak ill
of the dead?

11:24.400 --> 11:25.435
When I'm done with you,

11:25.520 --> 11:28.273
you will be begging Edric,
son of Walter, for mercy.

11:29.840 --> 11:30.875
Walter?

11:31.920 --> 11:33.194
<i>(ROARS)</i>

11:36.440 --> 11:39.273
Your father was Walter?

11:43.080 --> 11:44.195
You knew him.

11:45.400 --> 11:50.918
Your father was the only beloved son
of King Gareth and Queen Rhonu.

11:51.560 --> 11:54.234
Come on. Higher.

11:54.800 --> 11:59.192
<i>DRAGO: But Walter had no interest in
following the path of knighthood.</i>

11:59.320 --> 12:00.310
Father!

12:00.440 --> 12:02.556
<i>DRAGO: Though his father
loved Walter,</i>

12:02.640 --> 12:06.474
<i>running a kingdom and helping
me raise seven dragons</i>

12:06.560 --> 12:10.155
<i>took more time from the boy
than he appreciated.</i>

12:11.440 --> 12:16.469
<i>Naturally, Walter took to his
mother's Celtic independence.</i>

12:19.120 --> 12:22.636
Let's do a throw together.

12:23.480 --> 12:25.232
(BOTH LAUGHING)

12:34.760 --> 12:39.357
<i>DRAGO: When tragedy killed the
dragon with whom she was bonded,</i>

12:39.440 --> 12:41.636
<i>Walter was devastated.</i>

12:42.760 --> 12:45.513
<i>The King was away, I was
going to bring him back,</i>

12:45.640 --> 12:48.837
<i>but before I could, your
father had made up his mind.</i>

12:48.960 --> 12:49.995
Get back!

12:50.520 --> 12:52.431
You say you're here
to bring peace,

12:52.520 --> 12:54.750
but dragons have done
nothing but take from me.

12:55.520 --> 12:58.273
<i>DRAGO: He disappeared
without a trace.</i>

12:58.600 --> 13:01.991
<i>We searched,
but we never found him.</i>

13:02.320 --> 13:07.440
DRAGO: Your father was heir to the throne.
You are next in line.

13:07.960 --> 13:09.792
He never spoke
about his childhood.

13:11.200 --> 13:13.316
We lived so deep
in the forest.

13:15.480 --> 13:17.391
Maybe he thought that if
we were near the castle

13:17.480 --> 13:18.800
that I'd find out
the truth?

13:19.160 --> 13:20.878
(TRUMPETS BLOWING)

13:21.040 --> 13:23.156
EDRIC: Whoa. Hello.

13:23.400 --> 13:24.799
(CHUCKLES)

13:26.400 --> 13:28.232
Whoa. Sorry.
Nice to meet you. Welcome.

13:29.560 --> 13:31.949
Hello. These doors?

13:32.080 --> 13:33.309
Please.

13:34.880 --> 13:36.553
COUNCILOR MARRAKAR:
The royal courtyard.

13:38.240 --> 13:39.639
Big. (CHUCKLES)

13:42.040 --> 13:44.316
OSMUND: And the famed
castle murals.

13:57.320 --> 14:01.518
COUNCILOR MARRAKAR: Are we to
simply believe that he is the heir?

14:02.720 --> 14:05.030
Look, I don't blame you
for being cautious.

14:06.080 --> 14:09.436
And damn me if I'll ever
trust a dragon,

14:09.520 --> 14:11.591
but somehow I feel
what he says is true.

14:18.720 --> 14:20.074
It's the bond.

14:21.440 --> 14:22.874
If he feels it,

14:23.560 --> 14:24.914
Drago feels it,

14:25.600 --> 14:26.954
<i>it must be true.</i>

14:36.360 --> 14:39.273
First, my capable Sheriff.

14:39.440 --> 14:42.478
Now, My Liege.

14:53.320 --> 14:54.310
Um...

14:56.120 --> 14:57.793
(STAMMERS) I'm... One moment.

15:09.080 --> 15:10.309
Your Majesty?

15:12.440 --> 15:14.829
Everyone will understand
if this is too much for you.

15:14.920 --> 15:17.992
I knew it. I knew I was meant to
do more than simply hide away.

15:18.120 --> 15:21.078
To use my strength
for a greater cause.

15:21.600 --> 15:22.635
I'm King?

15:24.240 --> 15:25.514
I'm King.

15:31.960 --> 15:33.598
(SHOUTS) I'm King!

15:37.800 --> 15:41.191
DRAGO: Your grandfather surveyed
the kingdom from the air.

15:41.320 --> 15:43.675
Let me give you a ride,
it's faster.

15:43.760 --> 15:47.674
We can use the time to better
understand the bond between us.

15:47.840 --> 15:50.354
I'll take my chances
on the ground, thanks.

15:51.120 --> 15:52.519
Good Lord.

15:52.960 --> 15:56.112
Here you go. (WHISTLES)
Some bread for you.

15:56.200 --> 15:57.838
(CHUCKLES)

15:59.360 --> 16:00.475
Hmm?

16:00.560 --> 16:03.279
My Liege, some documents
need your attention.

16:03.840 --> 16:05.399
If you'd be so kind.

16:07.800 --> 16:10.314
I'm really very strong. Have
you heard of my strength?

16:10.640 --> 16:11.710
I once destroyed a house.

16:12.520 --> 16:15.034
I sneezed on it, and it just fell apart.
(eneeuwe)

16:16.720 --> 16:18.154
(GRUNTS)

16:18.240 --> 16:19.310
(ALL CHEERING)

16:21.320 --> 16:23.072
(BLEATING)
Oh. Oh.

16:24.320 --> 16:25.549
An angry ram.

16:28.640 --> 16:29.914
EDRIC: I can't read.

16:30.520 --> 16:32.079
But you can sign.

16:32.200 --> 16:33.235
Yes, I can.

16:33.320 --> 16:34.993
But like a full-grown bull.

16:35.160 --> 16:36.480
(GIRLS GIGGLING)

16:37.520 --> 16:39.750
But he's been around with you
guys for a long time, hasn't he?

16:40.240 --> 16:41.674
<i>(CLEARS T HRO AT)</i>

16:48.240 --> 16:51.517
These papers require
your immediate attention.

16:59.840 --> 17:01.911
I want it to be strong
but sensitive.

17:02.880 --> 17:04.678
Regal yet relatable.

17:08.920 --> 17:10.354
Don't be subtle.

17:16.160 --> 17:17.877
(GRUNTS)

17:18.920 --> 17:22.276
(ALL CHEERING)
(LAUGHING)

17:36.680 --> 17:38.796
Well, listen, if you
need anything else...

17:41.320 --> 17:42.469
No.

17:47.560 --> 17:48.675
Come on.

17:51.120 --> 17:55.796
DRAGO: Do you realize you granted
the Earl an enormous gift of land?

17:57.120 --> 18:00.112
Yeah, we're friends.
Friends help each other.

18:00.600 --> 18:03.911
Something dragons might learn instead
of second-guessing all the time.

18:08.280 --> 18:13.434
Perhaps your bond
skipped a generation,

18:14.440 --> 18:18.274
passing over his father
and ending up in him.

18:18.760 --> 18:24.039
And your draconic blood has
given him this great strength.

18:24.120 --> 18:26.475
Yes, but how can you
explain the fact

18:26.560 --> 18:28.597
that he's an arrogant snout?

18:29.120 --> 18:30.633
(CHUCKLES)

18:34.680 --> 18:35.875
He's young.

18:38.000 --> 18:41.197
But we do not share
a full bond.

18:41.280 --> 18:43.840
He cannot feel my pain.

18:44.440 --> 18:47.239
OSMUND: You never felt him
all these years?

18:47.320 --> 18:49.960
Not until King Gareth passed.

18:50.040 --> 18:53.795
Yes. That bond was primary.

18:54.800 --> 18:58.555
Like... Like a bell,
loud and clear.

18:59.680 --> 19:02.069
You couldn't sense
this other connection until

19:06.480 --> 19:08.118
the bell went silent.

19:12.480 --> 19:14.312
Hello, hello.

19:14.400 --> 19:15.959
Hello. (CHUCKLES)

19:16.200 --> 19:18.316
Sorry about the mess.

19:20.320 --> 19:21.993
On, a bath? (CHUCKLES)

19:22.360 --> 19:24.033
Baths are for children.

19:24.600 --> 19:26.671
A man's smell is his soul.

19:29.680 --> 19:31.478
Well, off you go.

19:33.560 --> 19:34.595
Thanks.

19:39.680 --> 19:41.353
(DOOR CLOSES)

19:41.480 --> 19:43.551
"A man's smell is his soul"?

19:44.480 --> 19:46.391
Come on,
you can do better than that.

19:56.680 --> 19:58.159
DRAGO: How's the water?
(GASPS)

19:58.240 --> 19:59.310
(GROANS)

20:00.720 --> 20:02.552
A little privacy, please?

20:02.680 --> 20:04.398
Since you've been
avoiding me,

20:04.480 --> 20:06.790
I thought I'd make you
a captive audience.

20:06.880 --> 20:09.633
Yeah, well, I've been busy, haven't I?
Doing king stuff.

20:09.720 --> 20:11.393
Edric, you don't trust me.

20:11.520 --> 20:13.193
You got that
from your father

20:13.280 --> 20:16.159
<i>as</i> surely as the scales on
your back came from me.

20:16.680 --> 20:21.880
As our bond grows, it will be harder
and harder to hide things from me.

20:21.960 --> 20:23.473
I'm not hiding anything.

20:23.640 --> 20:24.710
Swear.

20:26.560 --> 20:27.595
I swear.

20:28.080 --> 20:29.400
Ow!

20:30.120 --> 20:31.713
You yellow-eyed...

20:32.880 --> 20:33.950
Ow.

20:34.120 --> 20:38.990
I can feel your heart, but we
do not share pain of the flesh.

20:39.080 --> 20:41.037
Half of our bond is missing.

20:41.640 --> 20:43.870
I want to know why.

20:48.200 --> 20:49.873
I had a twin sister.

21:09.840 --> 21:10.875
Get off.

21:12.840 --> 21:14.513
EDRIC: As hard as
my childhood was...

21:14.600 --> 21:16.159
Stay in the cart.

21:16.240 --> 21:17.389
EDRIC:
...Mehgan had <i>it</i> worse.

21:17.480 --> 21:20.472
VVALTER: Keep your hood up. Walk
where other people don't walk.

21:20.560 --> 21:21.675
Talk to no one.

21:21.800 --> 21:24.440
WOMAN: That's her!
Her brother's evil twin!

21:24.520 --> 21:25.555
Get out, get out.

21:25.680 --> 21:27.557
WOMAN: Are you going to
let her walk amongst us?

21:27.680 --> 21:28.795
WALTER: Get out.
She's cursed!

21:28.880 --> 21:29.915
What were you thinking?

21:30.000 --> 21:31.479
EDRIC: <i>Father lectured us
repeatedly about</i>

21:31.600 --> 21:32.999
<i>how a dragon had
poisoned our mother,</i>

21:33.080 --> 21:36.630
<i>eventually killing her and causing
these scales to grow on our bodies.</i>

21:37.600 --> 21:39.238
WALTER: Those damn scales.

21:39.360 --> 21:41.112
How many times
have I told you?

21:42.000 --> 21:43.991
Mehgan, keep your hood up.

21:55.160 --> 21:58.232
<i>EDRIC: We always used to stay up
/ate and watch the stars together.</i>

21:58.320 --> 22:00.357
Do you see it there?
Yeah.

22:00.560 --> 22:02.392
EDRIC:
There's the dragon star.

22:02.480 --> 22:03.959
The head.

22:04.040 --> 22:05.269
He lies in stone.

22:06.000 --> 22:07.479
The scales.

22:12.120 --> 22:14.634
(EDRIC WHISTLING)

22:16.280 --> 22:17.600
MEHGANI Help!

22:20.600 --> 22:21.954
Help!

22:22.040 --> 22:23.075
No!

22:25.120 --> 22:26.554
No!
Show us that sorcery.

22:26.640 --> 22:28.790
Do it again, girl. Do it!

22:28.880 --> 22:29.915
(GRUNTS)

22:35.480 --> 22:37.357
(GRUNTING)

22:43.120 --> 22:45.157
(YELLS)
(GASPS)

22:48.880 --> 22:50.359
What did he mean,
"Do it again"?

22:50.440 --> 22:51.839
Do what again?

22:53.360 --> 22:54.998
<i>EDRIC: Whereas my strength
grew with time,</i>

22:55.680 --> 22:58.274
<i>Mehgan discovered her talent
quite suddenly.</i>

23:21.640 --> 23:22.994
(ALL CHEERING)

23:28.600 --> 23:30.352
<i>Earl Robert noticed me.</i>

23:32.880 --> 23:35.633
<i>His Sheriff was getting old,
and he needed an apprentice.</i>

23:36.880 --> 23:39.713
<i>I couldn't wait to get home and
tell Father the good news.</i>

23:51.200 --> 23:52.235
Father!

23:52.800 --> 23:53.949
M99, what happened?

23:54.040 --> 23:55.713
He said we had to
move away because of me!

23:55.800 --> 23:56.949
Meg, get in there,
you can save him!

23:57.080 --> 23:58.832
It's too late! I got mad
at him and the flames,

23:58.920 --> 24:00.479
I couldn't control them.

24:00.560 --> 24:02.233
It was an accident.
I'm sorry!

24:02.360 --> 24:03.919
Oh. Meg...

24:05.280 --> 24:06.350
Meg.

24:06.440 --> 24:08.078
EDRIC: <i>The villagers
wasted no time.</i>

24:08.160 --> 24:10.754
WOMAN: The witch-girl
killed her father!

24:10.840 --> 24:13.753
Burned him alive!
She must hang!

24:14.160 --> 24:16.037
<i>EDRIC: I begged the Earl for
money to get her to safety</i>

24:16.120 --> 24:17.952
<i>where she could
make a new start.</i>

24:21.720 --> 24:25.270
<i>But in exchange,
I had to stay.</i>

24:28.040 --> 24:30.759
<i>I always felt like she was by
my side, even when she wasn't.</i>

24:32.440 --> 24:33.919
And now I don't.

24:35.960 --> 24:37.519
She's probably dead.

24:37.600 --> 24:39.432
I'm sorry, Edric.

24:40.080 --> 24:41.434
You couldn't feel pain
through my hands,

24:41.520 --> 24:43.193
so you had to feel it
through my heart, eh?

24:43.280 --> 24:44.953
DRAGO: That was not
my intention.

24:47.200 --> 24:50.670
Play music!
I don't live in the past.

24:51.800 --> 24:54.394
(INSTRUMENT PLAYING)

25:07.280 --> 25:08.953
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

25:10.800 --> 25:12.473
(GIGGLING)

25:12.800 --> 25:15.952
(MEN YELLING IN DISTANCE)

25:21.600 --> 25:23.034
(GROANS)

25:23.760 --> 25:25.592
(MEN YELLING)
(WOMEN SCREAMING)

25:41.600 --> 25:43.671
(CHOKING)

25:47.760 --> 25:49.273
You can't kill me.

25:49.960 --> 25:53.112
Odin himself gave me his blessing of fire.
(BCDNES CRACKING)

25:59.240 --> 26:00.958
PLAYER: Verily,
you did promise, sir,

26:01.080 --> 26:02.115
that my humble
cast of players

26:02.200 --> 26:05.795
could live in your stable
in exchange for performance.

26:06.520 --> 26:09.717
My Lord,
their plays make no sense.

26:09.880 --> 26:11.712
PLAYER: I wrote
the play myself, all right?

26:11.840 --> 26:13.035
It's on the theme of vanity.

26:13.280 --> 26:15.476
I play Mr. Vanity, who finds
himself, one night...

26:15.560 --> 26:16.595
Councilor?

26:16.720 --> 26:18.711
PLAYER: ...wandering through a
forest in search of the witch,

26:18.800 --> 26:19.835
the Witch of the Mountains.

26:19.920 --> 26:21.752
And the Witch of the
Mountains gives him a potion

26:21.840 --> 26:23.114
in exchange for
some coins and...

26:23.600 --> 26:25.955
My Lord,
don't listen to this.

26:26.040 --> 26:28.270
My Lord, ships have
landed on the coast.

26:28.360 --> 26:29.475
Yes?

26:29.560 --> 26:30.709
COUNCILOR MARRAKAR: Norsemen.

26:31.280 --> 26:32.634
Brilliant.

26:32.720 --> 26:36.998
My Lord, they are fierce warriors,
and they march this way.

26:37.080 --> 26:39.833
Yes! Excellent!
Bring my armor.

26:42.360 --> 26:43.953
And prepare the knights?

26:44.080 --> 26:46.071
The knights, them.
Prepare them.

26:50.920 --> 26:52.513
It's a good play.
It's rubbish.

26:56.840 --> 26:58.638
(ALL PANTING)

27:14.320 --> 27:15.355
(SNORTS)

27:29.960 --> 27:33.919
They're approaching fast,
just beyond the treeline now.

27:34.000 --> 27:36.640
I suggest you stand firm
with your soldiers

27:36.720 --> 27:38.552
and allow me to
talk with them.

27:38.640 --> 27:41.837
Talk? Just stand back
and look scary, dragon.

27:59.960 --> 28:00.995
(BATTLE CRY)

28:01.080 --> 28:04.152
(ALL YELLING)

28:16.200 --> 28:20.990
My Lord, use Drago now,
before it is too late.

28:33.000 --> 28:35.037
I am King Edric.

28:35.600 --> 28:38.638
I challenge your leader
to personal combat!

28:38.800 --> 28:40.950
(ALL YELLING)

29:10.880 --> 29:12.598
Shields up!
KNIGHTS: Shields!

29:22.520 --> 29:25.672
Have we got the side of a barn?
Maybe they can hit that!

29:25.880 --> 29:28.110
(ALL LAUGHING)

29:35.400 --> 29:36.913
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

29:39.760 --> 29:40.909
Steady.

29:46.480 --> 29:47.709
No, wait!

29:48.400 --> 29:49.435
(GRUNTS)

29:56.920 --> 29:57.955
It's...

29:58.440 --> 29:59.714
My sister.

30:06.280 --> 30:09.671
Hello, Brother.
Shall we talk?

30:20.520 --> 30:22.113
Shall I address you as...

30:22.400 --> 30:24.277
Mehgan.
Let's keep it simple.

30:24.360 --> 30:25.794
And you are
the wise Drago.

30:25.880 --> 30:27.029
DRAGO: "Wise"?

30:27.120 --> 30:28.235
(CHUCKUNG)

30:28.760 --> 30:31.274
I expected you to have
the same opinion

30:31.360 --> 30:33.715
of dragons as
your brother does.

30:35.080 --> 30:36.309
MEHGAN: Come on.

30:58.280 --> 30:59.679
(SIGHS)

31:02.040 --> 31:04.793
My mind-reading
is a little rusty.

31:04.880 --> 31:06.553
You might have to
use your words.

31:08.320 --> 31:10.072
All these years
I've wondered where you were,

31:10.160 --> 31:12.834
but leading an army of Vikings
never crossed my mind.

31:12.920 --> 31:15.480
Well, I've always been the
unpredictable one, haven%I?

31:16.880 --> 31:19.030
And yes, for the longest time

31:19.120 --> 31:21.794
I did have the same opinion
of dragons as my brother.

31:22.640 --> 31:25.154
But then,
I heard about a new king,

31:25.240 --> 31:26.992
with
the "strength of three men"

31:27.680 --> 31:28.829
and your name,

31:28.920 --> 31:32.356
who had inherited
the throne by birthright.

31:33.920 --> 31:35.957
And all our connections
fell into place.

31:36.760 --> 31:39.400
See, we're family.
All three of us.

31:40.800 --> 31:42.518
How could I curse
my own blood?

31:43.240 --> 31:45.072
Though you got
the better end of the deal.

31:45.160 --> 31:46.878
My talent is mostly
useful for barbecues.

31:47.360 --> 31:49.715
Yes, well,
you almost barbecued my men.

31:49.800 --> 31:52.440
You can fan the flames?
Grow them hotter?

31:52.880 --> 31:55.076
I can control the flames,
but I can't create them.

31:55.160 --> 31:56.480
How do you do it?

31:58.240 --> 32:00.390
The Heartfire.

32:01.040 --> 32:04.829
Source of our breath,
and the life-giving force

32:04.920 --> 32:08.356
that a dragon can share
with someone of our choosing.

32:08.600 --> 32:10.591
Its fire sustains us.

32:11.160 --> 32:15.677
Perhaps I could teach you
how to develop your talent.

32:17.520 --> 32:18.840
In time.

32:21.840 --> 32:24.354
But that's assuming
you've come in peace.

32:26.240 --> 32:27.435
Have you come
in peace, Mehgan?

32:27.520 --> 32:28.874
That depends, Edric.

32:29.360 --> 32:30.839
On what?

32:30.920 --> 32:32.149
Do you remember
how Father used to

32:32.240 --> 32:33.389
tell me off for
playing tricks on you?

32:33.960 --> 32:36.759
"One minute older doesn't
make you one minute smarter."

32:37.200 --> 32:39.714
I'm sorry, my mind-reading's
a little rusty.

32:41.400 --> 32:43.038
I am firstborn.

32:44.280 --> 32:45.395
I should be Queen.

32:46.560 --> 32:48.039
(CHUCKLES)

32:49.120 --> 32:50.758
Uh, that's not...
Not what?

32:51.760 --> 32:53.353
I'm King.
That can't be undone.

32:53.440 --> 32:54.475
Step down.

32:55.280 --> 32:56.315
You can't sit on my throne.

32:56.400 --> 32:57.435
Because I'm a woman?

32:58.240 --> 32:59.275
You don't need
to say it.

32:59.560 --> 33:01.676
Do you think that if I had
your strength and you my fire,

33:01.760 --> 33:03.080
they would have
cheered for me

33:03.160 --> 33:04.992
and shunned you
when we were younger?

33:05.080 --> 33:06.718
I think not, little brother.

33:07.600 --> 33:09.989
Hold my sex
against me, or my scales,

33:10.080 --> 33:13.789
but if "birth" is "right,"
then I am Queen.

33:17.240 --> 33:18.389
(GASPS)

33:22.240 --> 33:23.753
You want to fight,
let's fight.

33:24.520 --> 33:26.272
Drago's fire trumps yours,

33:26.440 --> 33:29.717
and I'll toss your Vikings back
into the sea all by myself.

33:29.800 --> 33:32.599
DRAGO: I suggest
we sleep on it.

33:44.440 --> 33:45.635
(KICKS TABLE)

33:46.760 --> 33:48.034
(SHOUTS)

35:05.080 --> 35:06.400
<i>(CLEARS T HRO AT)</i>

35:07.200 --> 35:09.714
I can feel
you're not sleeping.

35:14.520 --> 35:17.273
And now I can feel
you're faking it.

35:19.040 --> 35:21.475
How am I supposed to sleep
when you're talking?

35:21.560 --> 35:23.710
She got under your skin.

35:24.400 --> 35:26.676
There's dragonheart
in both of you.

35:26.760 --> 35:28.558
Passionate, yes,

35:28.640 --> 35:33.157
but for those who are worthy
it can do wondrous things.

35:34.080 --> 35:37.311
I couldn't help
your father, Edric,

35:37.400 --> 35:40.040
but if you and your sister
can put aside...

35:40.200 --> 35:41.873
Maybe you should
stick to raising dragons.

35:42.000 --> 35:44.116
Humans haven't quite worked
out for you, havethey?

35:46.600 --> 35:48.432
Good night, Your Majesty.

36:18.800 --> 36:20.916
(SNORING)

36:43.800 --> 36:45.916
(CONTINUES SNORING)

36:52.800 --> 36:53.995
(GROANS)

37:35.040 --> 37:36.110
KNIGHT: Guards!

37:39.520 --> 37:40.715
KNIGHT 2: We're under attack!

37:41.000 --> 37:42.638
(ALL GRUNTING)

37:49.720 --> 37:50.869
Edric!

37:57.200 --> 37:58.679
COUNCILOR MARRAKAR:
My King, look out!

37:59.200 --> 38:00.235
(GRUNTS)

38:00.920 --> 38:02.399
Councilor?

38:03.040 --> 38:04.189
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

38:05.040 --> 38:06.474
THORGRIM: Boy-king!

38:08.000 --> 38:09.354
You ready for a man's death?

38:23.240 --> 38:26.596
My breath...
The fire, it's gone!

38:26.880 --> 38:28.234
Men, behind me!

38:45.560 --> 38:46.595
(GROWLS)

38:50.760 --> 38:51.909
(GROANS)

38:52.080 --> 38:53.753
(GASPING)

38:54.240 --> 38:57.471
Hurts, doesn't it?

39:05.760 --> 39:06.795
(GRUNTS)

39:15.560 --> 39:18.154
(PANTING)

39:19.560 --> 39:21.278
Odin's flame.

39:25.120 --> 39:26.269
EDRICI Meg?

39:27.120 --> 39:29.794
Meg, stop.

39:35.120 --> 39:36.155
Meg!

39:38.520 --> 39:39.794
Stop!

39:58.520 --> 40:00.158
WARRIOR:
You're coming with me.

40:02.840 --> 40:04.513
Back! Stand there!

40:08.320 --> 40:09.754
So, just to be clear,

40:09.840 --> 40:12.798
she just walked right up
to you and took your fire?

40:12.880 --> 40:14.154
Just like that?

40:14.520 --> 40:15.635
That was easy.

40:18.800 --> 40:20.120
Get over there!
(GRUNTS)

40:22.000 --> 40:23.320
(GRUNTS)

40:23.520 --> 40:26.080
I mean, do you even count
as a dragon anymore?

40:26.160 --> 40:27.992
You're more like a worm.
Like a leggy worm...

40:28.840 --> 40:30.035
(GASPING)

40:30.160 --> 40:31.992
DRAGO: Well,
that shut you up.

40:32.680 --> 40:35.194
Seems his strength
nearly matches yours.

40:38.960 --> 40:40.030
Pray quickly.

40:43.080 --> 40:46.038
My Lord,
what are we going to do?

40:47.520 --> 40:50.558
Just don't make yourself a target.
I'll think of something.

40:50.680 --> 40:53.194
Why is she doing this?
She's your sister.

41:16.200 --> 41:17.998
Oh, come on!
(G ROANS)

41:20.720 --> 41:22.154
Kind of you
to stick around.

41:22.240 --> 41:26.199
I only agreed to ensure your
brother's life was spared.

41:26.280 --> 41:31.150
You will never truly possess the
Heartfire, you know that, don't you?

41:31.240 --> 41:33.959
If not possessing something
feels this good,

41:34.080 --> 41:35.798
may fortune rob me blind.

41:41.080 --> 41:42.229
Follow me.

41:44.080 --> 41:46.037
Come on, keep up.

41:50.440 --> 41:52.909
Reconsider,
my beautiful Fire Queen.

41:54.320 --> 41:58.757
Leaving him alive is allowing a
fox to run free among your hens.

41:58.880 --> 42:01.872
Then it's a good thing I
know a few wolves, isn't it?

42:08.960 --> 42:11.429
I believe your King
wishes to address you.

42:15.440 --> 42:16.919
(CROWD MURMURING)

42:24.520 --> 42:25.840
(SOFTLY) I hereby
abdicate the throne...

42:25.960 --> 42:28.793
That's going to
have to be much louder.

42:32.520 --> 42:35.512
(LOUDLY) I hereby
abdicate the throne...

42:35.800 --> 42:36.949
MAN: No!

42:38.320 --> 42:41.756
...and acknowledge the birthright
of my elder sister, Mehgan...

42:41.840 --> 42:43.592
Queen Mehgan.

42:46.840 --> 42:48.797
Queen Mehgan.

42:51.440 --> 42:53.158
Long may she reign.

42:57.440 --> 42:58.430
(EDRIC GROANS)
(RIPS)

42:58.520 --> 43:01.160
(CROWD EXC LAIMING)

43:02.040 --> 43:03.110
MAN: He bears the mark!

43:04.800 --> 43:07.997
So, you see,
we're not so different.

43:19.960 --> 43:26.150
Do you solemnly swear to justly
govern the people of Lundenwic?

43:26.240 --> 43:28.151
I solemnly swear.

44:02.480 --> 44:03.834
Englishmen,

44:05.520 --> 44:08.034
the Norsemen are more
like you than it seems.

44:08.400 --> 44:11.153
They will work
in the fields alongside you,

44:11.240 --> 44:15.916
and together we will
grow strong and prosper.

44:16.960 --> 44:19.759
For my first decree as Queen,

44:21.080 --> 44:25.870
I banish you, Edric, from
this town and all its shires.

44:26.400 --> 44:27.799
(ALL EXCLAIM)
MAN: No, no!

44:27.920 --> 44:28.910
Go.

44:30.240 --> 44:33.232
(CROWD SHOUTING
DISAPPROVINGLY)

44:42.440 --> 44:43.589
Okay-

44:50.760 --> 44:52.751
(PEOPLE SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

44:54.440 --> 44:57.592
Make sure
the King never returns.

44:57.680 --> 44:58.715
Mmm.

45:37.800 --> 45:40.269
The royal bedchamber,
Your Majesty.

45:42.520 --> 45:44.830
(CHICKEN CLUCKING)

45:49.480 --> 45:50.834
Boys.

45:52.760 --> 45:53.830
Clear everything out.

45:56.160 --> 45:57.992
(SNIFFLES)

46:00.960 --> 46:01.995
What?

46:02.080 --> 46:03.912
M'lady?
Are you in pain?

46:04.000 --> 46:06.355
No, m'lady.
Crying means pain.

46:06.440 --> 46:07.589
Orjoy. Which is it?

46:07.680 --> 46:08.829
My fiancé. ..
Joy, then.

46:08.960 --> 46:10.109
No...
Outwith it!

46:10.200 --> 46:13.830
(SOBBING) He's just... We are to be
married in a fortnight. But he's...

46:13.920 --> 46:14.910
Cruel?

46:15.040 --> 46:18.670
Yes. And old,
and a little hairy.

46:19.040 --> 46:20.269
Hmm.

46:20.520 --> 46:22.955
He says I'm useless, but
I'll do for making children.

46:23.880 --> 46:25.200
And you did not choose him?

46:25.280 --> 46:27.191
No, it was

46:28.440 --> 46:29.510
arranged.

46:32.560 --> 46:33.550
Very well.

46:36.800 --> 46:38.359
It is now un-arranged.

46:41.720 --> 46:43.040
By order of the Queen.

47:12.480 --> 47:15.916
Don't you see your rightful King is here?
Bring food, quickly!

47:16.000 --> 47:16.990
SERVANT: Yes, My Lord.

47:17.080 --> 47:18.673
Sit, My Lord.
SERVANT: Right away.

47:27.400 --> 47:29.914
You're not safe until you're
away from the shires.

47:30.000 --> 47:31.070
If they find you...

47:31.760 --> 47:33.558
I know this land
better than they do.

47:34.240 --> 47:37.278
And besides, there are over a hundred
homes here that will give me shelter.

47:38.040 --> 47:40.031
The Vikings are many.

47:40.120 --> 47:42.111
And your sister now wields
tremendous power.

47:42.240 --> 47:43.878
Let me worry about her.

47:52.240 --> 47:53.958
Do you still have the weapons
in the granary?

47:55.240 --> 47:56.958
I always have a backup.
ExceHenL

47:57.640 --> 47:58.789
You two,
you go to the villagers,

47:58.880 --> 48:00.359
you get extra men, and you
bring them back here.

48:00.480 --> 48:01.629
Go, now.
Sire.

48:07.320 --> 48:08.754
To loyal friends.

48:18.320 --> 48:21.119
EARL ROBERT: There's enough
to arm 50 men,

48:21.200 --> 48:24.079
and more in the stores
in the east field.

48:25.200 --> 48:27.874
We need horses. And we need
more armor for the men.

48:28.000 --> 48:29.354
Move and we shoot.

48:31.080 --> 48:32.718
I'm sorry, Edric.

48:34.200 --> 48:37.750
You're strong. But arrows are faster.
(CHUCKLES)

48:39.000 --> 48:42.118
Are the holdings and titles
I gave you worth nothing?

48:42.200 --> 48:44.840
To an earl who harbors
a fugitive?

48:46.680 --> 48:48.159
You should have kept running.

48:49.720 --> 48:50.869
Not in my nature.

48:51.000 --> 48:54.197
Even an animal
learns eventually.

48:55.880 --> 48:57.393
(MUFFLED GRUNTS)

48:59.400 --> 49:02.279
Property ownership, dowries,
village council votes,

49:02.360 --> 49:05.239
I want to see all the law books
where one's sex is specified.

49:05.360 --> 49:06.953
That's nearly
all of them.

49:07.040 --> 49:09.111
Great. Well,
we'd better bring a lunch.

49:10.360 --> 49:11.475
Your fire's lit early.

49:11.560 --> 49:12.595
I have much to do.

49:13.360 --> 49:14.839
Now, I've negotiated
for the tenants

49:14.920 --> 49:16.797
west of the river
to relocate.

49:16.880 --> 49:19.076
That's over 1,000 hectares
of the most fertile land

49:19.200 --> 49:21.157
for your men
and their families to farm.

49:21.240 --> 49:23.231
Yeah, it's good,
black earth.

49:23.880 --> 49:26.156
But my countrymen are
laughing at this idea

49:26.240 --> 49:29.710
that everyone is to be
treated exactly the same.

49:32.280 --> 49:33.759
Let them laugh.

49:34.880 --> 49:38.032
Just remember that when we
set sail, I needed an army.

49:38.560 --> 49:39.755
And that now,

49:41.400 --> 49:42.754
lam one.

49:53.920 --> 49:55.274
MEHGAN: Good morning, ladies.

49:55.400 --> 49:56.549
LADIES: Good morning.

49:56.680 --> 49:58.751
I've decided it's time
you learn a lesson.

50:00.920 --> 50:03.753
The Norsewomen have a tradition
of arming themselves.

50:03.840 --> 50:06.753
They do not ask for respect,
they take it.

50:07.120 --> 50:08.394
Let's begin.

50:08.480 --> 50:10.756
I strike, you block.

50:11.920 --> 50:13.115
(GRUNTS)

50:13.800 --> 50:14.915
Again.

50:17.200 --> 50:18.270
Again.

50:19.360 --> 50:20.634
(GRUNTS)

50:22.440 --> 50:23.475
Useless.

50:29.320 --> 50:30.879
(SHOUTS)
(GRUNTS)

50:34.480 --> 50:37.438
Let man nor woman
talk to you like that.

50:38.160 --> 50:39.798
Life is cruel.

50:42.280 --> 50:44.635
You must be prepared
to be crueler.

50:48.200 --> 50:49.998
(GRUNTING)

51:00.360 --> 51:01.794
(GASPING)

51:02.200 --> 51:03.918
You make good slave
in my home.

51:04.000 --> 51:05.354
No, no, no, I made
a deal with your Queen.

51:05.480 --> 51:07.471
She's not our Queen.

51:30.520 --> 51:32.158
VILLAGER:
Here you go, Drago.

51:35.160 --> 51:36.389
WOMAN: My Lady.

51:38.280 --> 51:40.191
VILLAGER 1: By your grace,
My Queen.

51:40.280 --> 51:41.509
VILLAGER 2: Good day.

51:44.680 --> 51:46.193
(SNORTS)

51:46.760 --> 51:48.159
Lost your appetite?

51:48.240 --> 51:51.358
I feel cold
without the Heartfire.

51:52.560 --> 51:54.198
I'm not myself.

51:57.680 --> 51:59.398
I'm feeling more myself
than ever.

51:59.880 --> 52:02.394
It's like the first time
ltouchedfwe without burning.

52:03.360 --> 52:05.112
I finally had an advantage.

52:05.760 --> 52:07.637
But it wasn't enough,
was it?

52:07.720 --> 52:12.112
You were already unpopular. The
fire has made you more so.

52:13.400 --> 52:14.390
What would you know?

52:14.480 --> 52:16.915
You couldn't even sense our
bond until we both shed blood.

52:17.040 --> 52:20.510
Nothing about the bond
seems the same with twins.

52:20.600 --> 52:23.035
And I know only what
your brother told me.

52:23.440 --> 52:26.114
(SCOFFS) What he doesn't
know could fill the sea.

52:29.160 --> 52:30.275
Why?

52:31.080 --> 52:32.400
What did he tell you?

52:33.560 --> 52:37.838
That being separated has put
a distance between you.

52:44.400 --> 52:46.869
<i>MEHGAN: Being separated
had little to do with it.</i>

52:46.960 --> 52:48.109
Meg?

52:48.600 --> 52:49.715
(SCOFFS) But you don't
have to hide.

52:50.240 --> 52:51.514
EDRIC: It's different.

52:51.600 --> 52:53.671
Why? They're not scared of me.

52:56.800 --> 52:58.199
<i>MEHGAN: Because he could
hide his scales,</i>

52:58.320 --> 53:00.038
<i>he became part of
the life of the town.</i>

53:01.320 --> 53:04.233
<i>While I spent more
and more time by myself.</i>

53:04.320 --> 53:05.515
<i>Practicing.</i>

53:06.640 --> 53:08.950
<i>Learning to bend
the flame to my will.</i>

53:20.840 --> 53:23.070
(CHUCKLES)

53:28.040 --> 53:29.394
<i>EDRIC: Meg, what happened?</i>

53:30.040 --> 53:34.193
The witch-girl killed her father!
She must hang!

53:41.560 --> 53:43.517
(THUNDER BOOMING)

53:44.040 --> 53:46.759
FISHERMAN:
The current is too strong!

53:46.840 --> 53:49.559
It's taking us out to sea!

53:51.840 --> 53:53.239
(SCREAMS)

53:53.440 --> 53:55.078
(GASPS)

53:56.760 --> 53:58.751
<i>MEHGAN: The storm set me
adrift for days.</i>

54:12.480 --> 54:15.518
(CATTLE SOUNDING)

54:28.440 --> 54:29.999
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

54:38.760 --> 54:41.434
(MEHGAN BREATHING HEAVILY)

54:47.120 --> 54:49.236
(WHIMPERS)

54:51.120 --> 54:53.953
WOMAN: Hmm. She will fetch
a good price.

54:57.240 --> 54:58.594
(GRUNTS)

54:58.720 --> 55:00.074
(PEOPLE EXCLAIM)

55:03.480 --> 55:05.312
(ALL EXCLAIM)

55:05.600 --> 55:07.511
(CROWD MURMURING
INDISTINCTLY)

55:24.840 --> 55:26.672
OSMUND: Excuse me, My Queen.

55:28.840 --> 55:30.239
I was just leaving.

55:30.320 --> 55:33.950
DRAGO: Queen Mehgan, when you
were born, you inherited a gift,

55:34.040 --> 55:37.351
a dragonheart's power
to bond with another.

55:37.440 --> 55:41.718
But this power comes from
giving up a part of yourself.

55:41.800 --> 55:43.837
When you only
take something,

55:43.920 --> 55:48.596
you build a wall between yourself
and those who care about you.

55:48.680 --> 55:50.000
(SCOFFS)

55:50.080 --> 55:52.356
If I want a child's lesson,

55:54.040 --> 55:55.474
I'll go to the priest.

56:06.040 --> 56:07.075
All clear.

56:50.400 --> 56:52.073
(GRUNTING)

56:53.480 --> 56:55.073
SLAVE: We're taking water!

56:55.160 --> 56:57.834
NORSEMAN: Hit it with the plunger!
Buckets, quickly!

56:59.280 --> 57:00.600
Captain?

57:05.480 --> 57:06.834
Strength of three men.

57:10.080 --> 57:11.275
(GROANS)

57:13.600 --> 57:14.635
(CHUCKLES)

57:16.680 --> 57:18.273
Uh, um...

57:18.760 --> 57:20.034
NORSEMAN: Die now.

57:22.000 --> 57:23.035
(GRUNTS)

57:23.120 --> 57:25.396
Come on, come on. Whoa.

57:25.600 --> 57:28.592
(GROWLING)
(NORSEMEN YELLING)

57:30.480 --> 57:32.949
DRAGO: Edric! Grab hold!

57:35.440 --> 57:36.919
(GRUNTS)

57:37.080 --> 57:38.400
(ALL YELLING)

57:43.480 --> 57:45.437
Come on.
Help him up.

57:48.600 --> 57:51.035
NORSEMAN: Don't pull him out.
We'll sink!

57:54.120 --> 57:55.190
Row.

58:10.000 --> 58:12.674
Looks like Odin's favor
has abandoned you.

58:15.800 --> 58:21.910
I wouldn't expect you to understand
the ways of the gods, Krokr.

58:27.680 --> 58:30.638
First, you allow
the King to leave.

58:30.720 --> 58:33.758
And now, there's a serpent
waiting for us in the dark,

58:33.840 --> 58:36.275
ready to devour us,
one by one.

58:37.600 --> 58:41.958
So far, this deal with the
Fire Queen has given us what?

58:42.720 --> 58:44.199
A few farms?

58:46.200 --> 58:49.591
We bring the blood
and swords for what?

58:49.680 --> 58:51.318
To become Englishmen?

58:52.040 --> 58:57.433
If you were leader, you
would understand patience.

58:58.920 --> 59:00.399
Pafience“.

59:00.480 --> 59:03.359
You only know patience because
you get to stoke her fires!

59:03.440 --> 59:05.192
(GRUNTING)

59:08.800 --> 59:10.871
THORGRIM:
What did you say? Huh?

59:11.120 --> 59:12.838
Did I ask you to speak?

59:13.080 --> 59:14.479
(SPEAKING NORWEGIAN)

59:15.040 --> 59:16.872
MEHGAN: Enough!
(KROKR COUGHS)

59:17.920 --> 59:19.115
This is a tribal matter.

59:19.240 --> 59:20.594
In my castle.

59:21.800 --> 59:23.552
We should have
clipped the dragon's wings.

59:26.720 --> 59:29.075
Drago's a dog
without his bark.

59:30.120 --> 59:31.633
Let him run astray.

59:41.520 --> 59:43.670
THORGRIM:
I've been blind, Leiknarr.

59:46.200 --> 59:47.759
But now I see.

59:48.920 --> 59:53.756
Find all the gold and silver
in the castle, in the town,

59:54.280 --> 59:55.873
and pick the best women.

59:56.520 --> 59:57.555
When do we sail?

59:58.720 --> 01:00:01.758
THORGRIM: When I have taken what
Odin truly sent her to give us.

01:00:03.600 --> 01:00:05.193
(GRUNTS)

01:00:13.480 --> 01:00:15.437
(GRUNTING)

01:00:20.040 --> 01:00:23.112
You see the dragon shape
in the stars?

01:00:26.400 --> 01:00:27.674
Draco.

01:00:28.240 --> 01:00:33.314
The eternal resting ground
for dragons who are worthy.

01:00:39.600 --> 01:00:41.750
You're worried that
you won't gain a place.

01:00:43.360 --> 01:00:46.512
(FLUTE PLAYING) PLAYER: "The wheel
of fortune turns and turns,

01:00:46.600 --> 01:00:49.718
"one's raised up
while another one burns."

01:00:52.440 --> 01:00:54.158
(FLUTE STOPS PLAYING)

01:01:02.520 --> 01:01:03.715
It's the King!

01:01:04.400 --> 01:01:05.674
(CHUCKLES)

01:01:08.360 --> 01:01:09.395
You're fine.

01:01:10.040 --> 01:01:11.314
(ALL EXCLAIM)

01:01:11.680 --> 01:01:13.273
The scenery comes alive!

01:01:13.360 --> 01:01:14.634
EDRIC: It's good, isn't it?

01:01:15.600 --> 01:01:16.829
Marvelous!

01:01:26.080 --> 01:01:27.309
YOUNG MEHGAN:
Are you watching?

01:01:32.400 --> 01:01:33.720
(PANTS)

01:01:34.800 --> 01:01:35.835
(CHUCKLES)

01:01:41.920 --> 01:01:43.911
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:01:49.280 --> 01:01:51.590
<i>WALTER: It's that tainted
blood within your veins.</i>

01:01:52.440 --> 01:01:53.589
<i>MEHGAN: How do you know
it's tainted?</i>

01:01:53.920 --> 01:01:55.479
We might be blessed.

01:01:55.560 --> 01:01:56.709
You don't know...
Quiet!

01:02:00.120 --> 01:02:01.554
(SLAMS DOOR)

01:02:05.120 --> 01:02:06.269
What's wrong with me?

01:02:07.920 --> 01:02:09.831
Why can't I be
like everybody else?

01:02:15.560 --> 01:02:17.358
(TWIG SNAPS)
(GASPS)

01:02:20.960 --> 01:02:23.918
KENDRA: Anything
before sleep, My Queen?

01:02:36.120 --> 01:02:37.633
(FLUTE PLAYING)

01:02:38.640 --> 01:02:40.631
(CHUCKLES)
(CHAINS RATTLE)

01:02:40.880 --> 01:02:44.396
Free at last, milord, free at last.
(BREATH ES VVITH RELIEF)

01:02:44.480 --> 01:02:46.471
Why, thanks.

01:02:49.400 --> 01:02:51.437
And if I were King, I
would build you a stage.

01:02:52.160 --> 01:02:53.798
The world
is my stage, milord.

01:02:54.400 --> 01:02:56.311
And milord
you shall ever be.

01:02:57.160 --> 01:03:01.074
Now, if you'll excuse me, that
flautist is criminally pitchy.

01:03:01.160 --> 01:03:02.355
Yeah.

01:03:03.880 --> 01:03:07.077
Be quiet! You're misbehaving.
(CHUCKUNG)

01:03:07.880 --> 01:03:09.678
I didn't expect that
to work.

01:03:10.680 --> 01:03:12.512
It's nice to know someone
still thinks I'm King.

01:03:12.760 --> 01:03:14.353
(DRAGO COUGHING)

01:03:15.000 --> 01:03:17.514
We'll find more like him.
(CONTINUES COUGHING)

01:03:17.720 --> 01:03:21.475
Let's face it,
my throne was a hollow one.

01:03:23.320 --> 01:03:25.516
People I depended on
betrayed me.

01:03:27.520 --> 01:03:29.955
I don't think I've ever made
any real friends except you.

01:03:30.720 --> 01:03:33.553
And I was awful to you, and
yet you came to my rescue.

01:03:33.640 --> 01:03:37.429
Friends.
I like the sound of that.

01:03:38.200 --> 01:03:40.714
More than friends.
We're family.

01:03:41.400 --> 01:03:43.198
Meg was right
about that at least.

01:03:48.240 --> 01:03:50.277
I'll try
not to fail you, too.

01:03:51.320 --> 01:03:53.118
DRAGO: Whom have you failed?

01:03:54.280 --> 01:03:58.069
My sister hates me, Vikings
have overrun the kingdom,

01:04:01.120 --> 01:04:03.475
and I've not been
entirely truthful with you.

01:04:04.200 --> 01:04:05.395
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:04:05.680 --> 01:04:08.957
<i>When I saw the fire, I wasn't
coming home, I was leaving.</i>

01:04:09.720 --> 01:04:11.233
(ALL CHEERING)

01:04:11.520 --> 01:04:12.840
Father? You won't believe...

01:04:12.920 --> 01:04:14.957
Gather your things.
We leave in the morning.

01:04:15.760 --> 01:04:17.239
What?
Someone spotted her.

01:04:17.320 --> 01:04:19.231
She was praying
to the fire.

01:04:20.040 --> 01:04:21.917
Where is she?
I sent her to hide.

01:04:22.840 --> 01:04:25.309
They're calling her
a witch now.

01:04:26.920 --> 01:04:28.319
No, no, no, Father,
I can%leave.

01:04:28.400 --> 01:04:30.630
Nonsense.
Gather your things.

01:04:30.760 --> 01:04:32.239
We'll leave tomorrow, and
head into the highlands...

01:04:32.320 --> 01:04:34.152
No! You don't understand.
I'm gonna be Sheriff.

01:04:34.400 --> 01:04:35.834
(GRUNTS)

01:04:36.600 --> 01:04:37.954
You will do as I say.

01:04:39.400 --> 01:04:40.720
Edflc?

01:04:41.880 --> 01:04:43.075
Edflc?

01:04:43.600 --> 01:04:45.273
Don't touch me.

01:04:55.120 --> 01:04:57.077
Father!
Meg, what happened?

01:04:57.160 --> 01:04:59.436
He said we had to move
away because of me.

01:04:59.920 --> 01:05:01.558
Father!
(GASPS)

01:05:02.600 --> 01:05:03.829
Meg, get in there,
you can save him!

01:05:04.000 --> 01:05:05.479
It's too late!

01:05:06.200 --> 01:05:09.591
The flames... I got mad at him,
and I couldn't control them!

01:05:10.320 --> 01:05:13.756
It was an accident.
I'm sorry.

01:05:18.920 --> 01:05:21.560
<i>EDRIC: I begged the Earl
for money,</i>

01:05:21.640 --> 01:05:23.551
<i>and I let Mehgan believe
I was going with her</i>

01:05:23.640 --> 01:05:25.551
<i>right up until
the last moment.</i>

01:05:25.840 --> 01:05:28.116
What?
I'm not coming.

01:05:28.200 --> 01:05:29.998
(VOICE BREAKING)
Why? What do you mean?

01:05:32.960 --> 01:05:34.633
Meg, I have a chance here.

01:05:36.600 --> 01:05:39.592
Well, then I'll stay, and we can
explain, and they'll listen to you.

01:05:39.680 --> 01:05:40.715
Meg, you killed him.

01:05:40.800 --> 01:05:42.029
No, you don't understand!

01:05:42.120 --> 01:05:43.713
You have to go!
Eddy“.

01:05:44.840 --> 01:05:46.194
Please.

01:05:46.920 --> 01:05:49.196
(SOBBING) No! Please.

01:05:49.280 --> 01:05:50.793
Snuff out the flame.

01:05:50.880 --> 01:05:52.871
Please, no!

01:06:08.160 --> 01:06:13.838
DRAGO: There is no pain like that
between those we love... (COUGHS)

01:06:14.040 --> 01:06:16.680
No pain. (COUGHING)

01:06:16.840 --> 01:06:18.035
<i>Bragg?</i>

01:06:19.320 --> 01:06:20.719
It is the Heartfire.

01:06:22.160 --> 01:06:25.994
I think I've been dying without
it, and I didn't even know.

01:06:26.080 --> 01:06:27.115
Then we have to
get it back.

01:06:27.200 --> 01:06:29.953
You must settle things with your sister.
The throne...

01:06:30.040 --> 01:06:32.600
She can have the throne.
We have to save you!

01:06:33.760 --> 01:06:37.196
Where does one
find this Heartfire?

01:06:38.440 --> 01:06:39.760
Can we be of some help?

01:06:41.880 --> 01:06:43.075
(FLUTE PLAYING)

01:06:43.200 --> 01:06:45.271
GIRL: The Players,
they're here!

01:06:47.960 --> 01:06:49.189
(EXCITED CHATTER)

01:06:49.600 --> 01:06:51.113
The Players are here!

01:07:04.280 --> 01:07:05.315
LEIKNARR:
What's this foolery?

01:07:05.400 --> 01:07:07.391
Why, foolery of
the first order.

01:07:07.480 --> 01:07:09.437
Come to cure
an evening of boredom

01:07:09.520 --> 01:07:15.391
with tales of blood, lust,
maybe even a dragon.

01:07:16.200 --> 01:07:17.315
What say you?

01:07:18.880 --> 01:07:19.915
Check the cart.

01:07:27.480 --> 01:07:28.515
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

01:07:48.600 --> 01:07:51.433
It's just an ordinary stone.
(CHUCKLES)

01:07:57.000 --> 01:07:58.434
Entertainment tax.

01:08:00.160 --> 01:08:01.150
Go on.

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:15.517
PLAYER: Tell me, Hermit, heard you
a tale more lamentable than mine?

01:08:15.600 --> 01:08:20.993
Stripped of my crown and
banished by my own cousin?

01:08:21.120 --> 01:08:25.353
If the hermit had family, it would
be the worst they could do to him.

01:08:25.800 --> 01:08:27.313
<i>(CROWD EXCLNM)</i>

01:08:27.520 --> 01:08:29.352
HERMIT: Wicked treachery!

01:08:30.160 --> 01:08:31.194
(GRUNTS)

01:08:36.880 --> 01:08:38.029
<i>(CROWD EXCLNM)</i>

01:08:49.840 --> 01:08:50.955
<i>(CROWD EXCLNM)</i>

01:08:53.040 --> 01:08:56.270
Oh, poor Prince.
Here, have my crown.

01:08:59.120 --> 01:09:01.031
(CROWD CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

01:09:03.720 --> 01:09:07.953
WOMAN: Bravo! Bravo!
Very good!

01:09:20.560 --> 01:09:22.073
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:09:30.760 --> 01:09:33.069
(CROWD EXC LAIMING)

01:09:33.200 --> 01:09:34.349
(SIGHS)

01:09:34.520 --> 01:09:37.990
And now,
an even bloodier tale!

01:09:38.080 --> 01:09:39.434
(ALL CHEERING)

01:09:39.760 --> 01:09:41.591
PLAYER:
Gather closer, friends.

01:09:42.359 --> 01:09:46.593
Come toward the light. For
out there in the darkness...

01:10:01.280 --> 01:10:03.271
(CROWD CHEERING IN DISTANCE)

01:10:07.080 --> 01:10:10.960
PLAYER: I hear tales of
witches in the nearby hills,

01:10:11.400 --> 01:10:13.630
unclean, cackling crones

01:10:14.120 --> 01:10:16.714
who tempt a traveler
with promise of wishes

01:10:16.800 --> 01:10:19.269
fulfilled only to ply them
with nightmares.

01:10:19.440 --> 01:10:21.875
(WHISPERS) Oy. I'm off.
Be ready.

01:10:21.960 --> 01:10:26.955
DRAGO: Hurry, I grow weaker
with every breath. (COUGHING)

01:10:27.160 --> 01:10:28.719
I'll get the Heartfire.
Count on it.

01:10:28.800 --> 01:10:31.314
PLAYER: I hear a traveler
coming at this very moment.

01:10:31.440 --> 01:10:33.272
Whatever will befall him?

01:10:33.480 --> 01:10:34.879
(russme)

01:10:35.080 --> 01:10:37.071
(CACKLING)

01:10:37.160 --> 01:10:38.719
Witch of the Mountains!

01:10:38.800 --> 01:10:42.156
I was born with
a face so horrid.

01:10:42.440 --> 01:10:47.992
Have my coin and give me a potion
that will make me beautiful.

01:10:48.120 --> 01:10:49.679
(CACKLING)

01:11:05.440 --> 01:11:06.999
(GROANS)

01:11:07.320 --> 01:11:09.357
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

01:11:09.520 --> 01:11:10.669
MAN: Excellent.

01:11:23.520 --> 01:11:25.352
MAN: Hey, hey, very good!
Hi.

01:11:27.720 --> 01:11:28.710
(GRUNTS)

01:11:29.960 --> 01:11:30.950
PLAYER: What's this?

01:11:31.040 --> 01:11:34.112
It is myself but beautiful.

01:11:34.200 --> 01:11:37.670
Now he will receive
the attention I crave.

01:11:39.040 --> 01:11:41.634
Lo! Another!

01:11:41.720 --> 01:11:44.553
Each one more beautiful
than the last.

01:11:46.120 --> 01:11:48.680
And now
they want to kill me.

01:11:51.840 --> 01:11:53.160
(GRUNTS)

01:12:33.760 --> 01:12:34.909
EDRICI Meg!

01:12:39.840 --> 01:12:40.875
(GRUNTS)

01:12:45.280 --> 01:12:46.759
I banished you!
How dare you?

01:12:46.880 --> 01:12:48.791
What? Save you?
"Thank you" would do.

01:12:48.960 --> 01:12:50.280
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:12:56.920 --> 01:12:58.718
(GROANS)

01:13:04.040 --> 01:13:05.235
No,no,no!

01:13:05.480 --> 01:13:07.312
(CACKLING)

01:13:07.960 --> 01:13:09.314
(CHEERING AND APPLAUDING)

01:13:09.440 --> 01:13:10.794
(WHISTLING)

01:13:13.080 --> 01:13:14.150
Hey!

01:13:19.760 --> 01:13:22.149
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

01:13:28.640 --> 01:13:30.119
Put out the fires!

01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:42.513
(PANTS)

01:13:43.280 --> 01:13:45.078
Thorgrim!
No!

01:13:46.080 --> 01:13:47.434
Catch!

01:13:53.840 --> 01:13:55.194
(GRUNTS)

01:13:58.920 --> 01:14:00.433
(GROANS)

01:14:03.840 --> 01:14:06.116
(PANTING)

01:14:06.200 --> 01:14:07.474
(ALL CHEERING)

01:14:07.800 --> 01:14:09.359
Yes!

01:14:09.960 --> 01:14:10.995
Yes.

01:14:11.960 --> 01:14:13.189
This is all your fault.

01:14:13.280 --> 01:14:14.429
Bring the Queen to me.

01:14:14.520 --> 01:14:16.238
This is my fault?
She was gonna kill you!

01:14:16.360 --> 01:14:17.794
I was trying to save you!
You ruined everything!

01:14:17.880 --> 01:14:19.279
I didn't need your help!

01:14:19.360 --> 01:14:21.033
She was gonna
kill you!

01:14:21.720 --> 01:14:23.791
Oh, great!
Now a load of Vikings.

01:14:23.880 --> 01:14:25.791
Please don't point that
so close to me.

01:14:25.880 --> 01:14:27.314
Go on then,
if you're so strong.

01:14:27.720 --> 01:14:28.710
I was trying to...

01:14:28.840 --> 01:14:30.717
(BOTH SCREAMING)

01:14:32.720 --> 01:14:34.233
MEHGAN: Tell him to
put us down!

01:14:34.320 --> 01:14:36.118
EDRIC: Do it, so I can
punch her in the face!

01:14:36.240 --> 01:14:37.310
DRAGO: Enough!

01:14:37.880 --> 01:14:38.870
(EDRIC SHOUTS)

01:15:24.160 --> 01:15:26.436
Feels like the first time
we tried wine.

01:15:27.640 --> 01:15:29.313
Yeah, just don't
puke on me again.

01:15:30.280 --> 01:15:31.270
Where are we?

01:15:32.840 --> 01:15:33.910
<i>And where's Drags'?</i>

01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:36.958
DRAGO: I must keep
my distance.

01:15:37.080 --> 01:15:39.435
(H EARTBEATS SOUNDING)

01:15:39.960 --> 01:15:41.314
You feel that?

01:15:41.840 --> 01:15:45.799
He's dying without his Heartfire,
stolen by a foolish Queen.

01:15:46.640 --> 01:15:48.551
Because a selfish King
wouldn't share his crown.

01:15:48.640 --> 01:15:50.153
DRAGO: I must keep
my distance,

01:15:50.280 --> 01:15:52.351
so I don't kill
the both of you!

01:15:52.480 --> 01:15:54.517
You were given a gift
at birth,

01:15:54.640 --> 01:15:57.758
a dragonheart, and someone
to share it with,

01:15:57.960 --> 01:16:01.590
someone who could understand you
and always be by your side.

01:16:01.800 --> 01:16:04.360
But instead,
you cut each other down.

01:16:04.480 --> 01:16:07.836
Tell me why I shouldn't end
your miserable lives?

01:16:08.000 --> 01:16:10.992
Such drama! You're worse
than those Players.

01:16:11.320 --> 01:16:15.314
You can't kill us. We're all bonded.
You'd be killing yourself.

01:16:15.440 --> 01:16:16.839
(MEHGAN GROANS)
Whoa.

01:16:17.160 --> 01:16:18.434
Just you, then.

01:16:18.520 --> 01:16:20.511
This bond of three
is unpredictable.

01:16:20.680 --> 01:16:22.796
Maybe two can survive
without the other!

01:16:22.880 --> 01:16:25.474
Drago, what happened
to "friends"? Mmm?

01:16:26.120 --> 01:16:27.997
"Family"? (GROANS)

01:16:29.480 --> 01:16:32.677
Being related to you is
dangerous to one's health!

01:16:32.800 --> 01:16:37.158
Your rivalry
must end, today. Now!

01:16:37.520 --> 01:16:40.672
And since nothing will be settled
until there is a victor,

01:16:41.040 --> 01:16:43.600
you will fight to the death.

01:16:43.680 --> 01:16:46.399
(CHUCKLES)
Winner takes all.

01:16:47.520 --> 01:16:49.158
Crown and kingdom.

01:16:55.240 --> 01:16:56.674
Okay-

01:16:58.360 --> 01:16:59.873
It's not a fair fight.

01:17:00.880 --> 01:17:02.678
No fire.
DRAGO: Here you go!

01:17:06.480 --> 01:17:07.834
Isn't there?

01:17:07.920 --> 01:17:09.319
Has it really
come to this?

01:17:09.400 --> 01:17:11.038
What are you? Scared?

01:17:11.160 --> 01:17:12.719
No! (GRUNTS)

01:17:13.360 --> 01:17:14.430
Do you know what?
I've never said this,

01:17:14.560 --> 01:17:15.550
but I really wish
you had been a brother.

01:17:15.680 --> 01:17:16.670
Why's that, Eddy?

01:17:16.760 --> 01:17:18.239
Because I would have
done this much sooner.

01:17:18.560 --> 01:17:19.595
(GRUNTS)

01:17:20.880 --> 01:17:22.234
Yeah, that felt good!

01:17:26.400 --> 01:17:27.674
And that was
only half-strength.

01:17:27.880 --> 01:17:30.076
(PANTING)

01:17:33.840 --> 01:17:35.069
EDRICI Whoa.

01:17:35.560 --> 01:17:36.880
(GRUNTS)

01:17:39.520 --> 01:17:40.749
That was a third.

01:17:41.560 --> 01:17:42.595
My shirt!

01:18:05.600 --> 01:18:06.670
(SHOUTS)

01:18:11.160 --> 01:18:12.275
(GROANS)

01:18:16.160 --> 01:18:17.434
(SHOUTS)

01:18:21.120 --> 01:18:22.599
Don't lose your head, sis!

01:18:23.600 --> 01:18:24.954
What if you win, Eddy?

01:18:25.240 --> 01:18:26.799
There's no one here
to applaud you.

01:18:27.280 --> 01:18:28.793
It's a hollow victory
for you.

01:18:29.120 --> 01:18:31.999
Me hollow? I'm not the one who
stole the crown. (SCOFFS)

01:18:32.840 --> 01:18:35.036
Grow up.
All I did was banish you.

01:18:35.120 --> 01:18:37.680
Just like you did to me.
Remember?

01:18:37.800 --> 01:18:40.110
Or are you trying to forget that,
like the scales on your back?

01:18:40.280 --> 01:18:41.395
And what about
your Viking lover?

01:18:41.480 --> 01:18:43.118
He forgot you
pretty quickly, didn't he?

01:18:43.520 --> 01:18:45.158
Vikings can be moody, yeah.

01:18:45.320 --> 01:18:46.958
Excellent judgment, Meg.

01:18:47.840 --> 01:18:50.514
If it wasn't for me,
you'd be dead!

01:18:50.640 --> 01:18:51.914
Oh, shut up!

01:19:03.480 --> 01:19:04.629
(GROANING)

01:19:08.320 --> 01:19:09.355
(GROANS)

01:19:10.160 --> 01:19:13.039
(BOTH GROANING)

01:19:25.320 --> 01:19:26.640
Meg.

01:19:38.560 --> 01:19:40.198
(LAUGHING)

01:19:57.200 --> 01:19:58.599
What do you want from us?

01:19:58.720 --> 01:20:01.234
DRAGO: Take responsibility
for what you've done!

01:20:01.400 --> 01:20:02.674
<i>MEHGAN: It's his to take!</i>

01:20:02.760 --> 01:20:03.795
No!

01:20:03.880 --> 01:20:05.314
<i>MEHGAN: He broke trust first.</i>

01:20:05.400 --> 01:20:08.233
I was saving you, like I always did!
You killed him!

01:20:09.920 --> 01:20:11.035
No, I didn't.

01:20:13.400 --> 01:20:15.710
What?
I didn't kill him.

01:20:16.880 --> 01:20:18.200
No, no, no, Father,
I can%leave.

01:20:18.280 --> 01:20:20.317
Nonsense,
gather your things.

01:20:20.400 --> 01:20:22.391
We'll leave tomorrow, we'll
head into the highlands...

01:20:22.520 --> 01:20:23.749
I'm going to be Sheriff!

01:20:24.720 --> 01:20:27.553
WALTER: You will do
as I say. Edric?

01:20:28.560 --> 01:20:29.755
(GASPS)

01:20:33.560 --> 01:20:34.755
(GASPING)

01:20:53.080 --> 01:20:54.070
I killed him.

01:20:55.880 --> 01:20:57.598
So you took the blame.

01:20:58.760 --> 01:21:00.239
<i>Why did you set
the house on fire?</i>

01:21:01.280 --> 01:21:03.954
<i>MEHGAN: Because you had
a chance to be someone.</i>

01:21:09.600 --> 01:21:12.672
<i>I used to lie awake
wishing that I was the son.</i>

01:21:12.800 --> 01:21:15.633
I let that wish
burn inside me.

01:21:18.440 --> 01:21:20.078
(LAUGHING)
And look at me now.

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:25.277
I've become that evil thing
they always said I was.

01:21:25.960 --> 01:21:28.349
I thought I was strong,
but I am not.

01:21:28.480 --> 01:21:31.120
No, Meg, no, you were stronger
than I ever could be.

01:21:31.280 --> 01:21:33.430
It wasn't your fault.
We were just children.

01:21:33.520 --> 01:21:34.919
But I should have known,

01:21:35.000 --> 01:21:37.594
I should have known then
and I still don't know,

01:21:38.760 --> 01:21:40.159
and now I've lost
the Heartfire,

01:21:40.280 --> 01:21:42.237
and it's costing you
your life.

01:21:42.320 --> 01:21:43.515
I'm sorry.

01:21:46.600 --> 01:21:47.999
I'm sorry.

01:21:54.120 --> 01:21:55.997
(SOBBING)

01:21:59.160 --> 01:22:03.518
The fight for the kingdom
is not over, my friends.

01:22:04.840 --> 01:22:09.357
<i>Even now the castle and
its people are in danger.</i>

01:22:11.880 --> 01:22:13.996
<i>Without the Heartfire,</i>

01:22:16.200 --> 01:22:19.431
I will not have enough
strength to help you.

01:22:19.520 --> 01:22:23.753
So, it's time for you,
the dragonhearted,

01:22:23.840 --> 01:22:26.354
to uphold the Code

01:22:27.480 --> 01:22:29.357
<i>to defend the helpless.</i>

01:22:31.360 --> 01:22:34.193
Undo the wicked.

01:22:36.040 --> 01:22:38.156
Yes.
(G ROAN S)

01:22:38.680 --> 01:22:40.876
Oh, I'm so sorry.
(GROANS)

01:23:02.120 --> 01:23:05.670
The women, where are they?

01:23:05.760 --> 01:23:06.875
That's all there is.

01:23:07.560 --> 01:23:09.312
You're hiding something.

01:23:11.400 --> 01:23:13.232
<i>THORGRWA: Odin's gift
is mine now.</i>

01:23:13.720 --> 01:23:17.953
We will travel home, and all
of Daneland will call me King!

01:23:18.400 --> 01:23:20.755
ALL: Yeah!

01:23:21.600 --> 01:23:24.752
(WHISTLING)

01:23:29.760 --> 01:23:32.434
There's a slight problem
with what you just said.

01:23:35.080 --> 01:23:36.991
To be king, you have
got to beat the King.

01:23:37.920 --> 01:23:38.910
Me.

01:23:41.280 --> 01:23:43.317
Okay, I'll be clearer
for you.

01:23:48.680 --> 01:23:50.591
I challenge you to a duel.

01:23:51.960 --> 01:23:54.429
(ALL CHEERING)

01:23:59.120 --> 01:24:00.155
Hmm?

01:24:00.440 --> 01:24:03.273
MAN: Come on, there's a fight!
There's a fight!

01:24:09.800 --> 01:24:12.474
(ALL CHEERING)

01:24:13.800 --> 01:24:16.189
Even your legendary strength
can't save you now.

01:24:19.120 --> 01:24:20.713
(SWO RD C LATTE RS)

01:24:21.520 --> 01:24:23.193
Someone tie
a hand behind my back!

01:24:24.800 --> 01:24:25.949
(CHEERING CONTINUES)

01:24:33.000 --> 01:24:34.149
That was very
thoughtful of you.

01:24:34.240 --> 01:24:35.389
Don't mention it.

01:24:45.480 --> 01:24:46.879
I need your help.

01:24:48.360 --> 01:24:50.317
Dkhftbfing the Queen along?
Nope.

01:24:50.400 --> 01:24:53.199
Kissing her ugly face is
like kissing a lizard's ass.

01:24:53.320 --> 01:24:55.152
Oh, come on,
that's my sister.

01:24:55.760 --> 01:24:56.989
And besides,
nobody wants to know

01:24:57.080 --> 01:24:58.354
what you get up to
with lizards.

01:24:58.440 --> 01:25:00.351
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:25:01.560 --> 01:25:02.834
Shut up!

01:25:06.280 --> 01:25:07.714
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:25:20.200 --> 01:25:22.510
(DRAGO GROWLS)

01:25:25.440 --> 01:25:30.116
Mehgan, Edric, hurry!
Get the Heartfire.

01:25:30.920 --> 01:25:32.069
Hold on, Drago.

01:25:41.600 --> 01:25:42.635
There she is!

01:25:58.280 --> 01:26:00.271
No fire. That's a shame.

01:26:00.840 --> 01:26:03.275
(WOMEN SHOUTING)
(MEN GROANING)

01:26:05.120 --> 01:26:07.236
(SWORDS CLATTERING)

01:26:25.960 --> 01:26:27.598
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:26:36.040 --> 01:26:37.075
(SPITS)

01:26:37.160 --> 01:26:38.355
Let's go.

01:27:22.000 --> 01:27:23.479
Sable, shoot the witch!

01:27:26.320 --> 01:27:27.833
EDRICI Meg!

01:27:31.400 --> 01:27:32.993
THORGRIM: Sable, shoot!

01:27:33.400 --> 01:27:34.470
(GROANS)

01:27:35.840 --> 01:27:37.319
Meg!

01:27:40.720 --> 01:27:41.755
(SHOUTS)

01:27:44.400 --> 01:27:46.038
(BREATH ES WEAKLY)

01:27:50.000 --> 01:27:51.399
<i>Drags.</i>

01:27:56.760 --> 01:27:58.353
(PANTING)

01:28:00.360 --> 01:28:01.350
(SHOUTING)

01:28:31.720 --> 01:28:32.869
(GRUNTING)

01:28:49.600 --> 01:28:53.958
Odin, grant me your gift.

01:29:24.480 --> 01:29:26.153
(SCREAMING)

01:29:27.440 --> 01:29:28.475
(SWORD SWISHING)

01:29:35.160 --> 01:29:37.356
(CROWD CLAMORING)

01:29:39.800 --> 01:29:40.835
(GASPS)

01:29:47.480 --> 01:29:48.800
(SOBBING)

01:29:49.480 --> 01:29:51.073
I've got you.
I've got you.

01:29:51.160 --> 01:29:53.515
I've got you.
Stay with me. Stay with me.

01:30:11.080 --> 01:30:13.356
(WHIMPERING)

01:30:30.960 --> 01:30:32.633
<i>Drags...</i>

01:30:35.600 --> 01:30:36.954
Take it.

01:30:37.040 --> 01:30:42.160
No, use the last of the Heartfire
to close Mehgan's wounds.

01:30:42.240 --> 01:30:44.470
I won't see you
separated again.

01:30:44.960 --> 01:30:48.112
But if you die,
so will we.

01:30:48.200 --> 01:30:49.395
Perhaps not.

01:30:49.880 --> 01:30:51.598
Reach out, Edric,

01:30:52.000 --> 01:30:55.550
offer the bond of your
dragonheart to your sister.

01:30:57.080 --> 01:31:01.995
If she does the same, then
together you may live on.

01:31:29.680 --> 01:31:31.034
Okay---...

01:31:33.480 --> 01:31:34.834
I've got to
take these out now.

01:31:38.000 --> 01:31:39.673
Ready?
(WINCES)

01:31:44.240 --> 01:31:45.435
(WINCES)

01:32:07.400 --> 01:32:08.720
(GROANS)

01:32:12.200 --> 01:32:13.429
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:32:13.680 --> 01:32:15.159
My strength.

01:32:18.640 --> 01:32:20.039
Just one man.

01:32:21.120 --> 01:32:22.315
Your face.

01:32:34.720 --> 01:32:35.755
(WINCES)

01:32:37.000 --> 01:32:38.035
It burns.

01:32:38.520 --> 01:32:39.669
<i>As Drags saw,</i>

01:32:41.240 --> 01:32:43.959
bonding is
giving something up

01:32:44.560 --> 01:32:47.313
and gaining so much more.

01:32:58.160 --> 01:32:59.992
<i>Thank you, Drags.</i>

01:33:00.080 --> 01:33:02.071
DRAGO: You're a family again.

01:33:04.840 --> 01:33:05.875
Yes, because of you.

01:33:07.000 --> 01:33:10.595
That is all I ever wanted.

01:34:01.560 --> 01:34:05.793
<i>DRAGO". Rule wisely together</i>

01:34:08.000 --> 01:34:10.560
<i>and listen to your hearts.</i>
